<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFC4FFE8A1987E35926A0C08" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC4FFE8A1987E35926A0C08" blockId="13.[145,761,1390,1658]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC4FFE8A1987E3591760FF5" box="[145,278,1391,1412]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Small to large adult-sized muscular 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC4FFE8A1987ED7914D0FD2" authorityName="PROSCH" authorityYear="1847" box="[145,301,1421,1443]" class="Cephalopoda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="13" pageNumber="1225" phylum="Mollusca" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Cranchioidea">Cranchioidea</taxonomicName>
with funnel–mantle locking apparatus modified into an inverted ‘T’ shape; buccal connectives attached to the dorsal borders of ventral arms; fins short and wide; ‘rhynchoteuthion’ paralarvae, with tentacles fused as a proboscis and with underdeveloped nervous, digestive and respiratory systems and arm crown at hatching relative to other cephalopod hatchlings; spherical, gelatinous egg masses.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
